The paper discusses a tool for managing and visualizing issue tracking in software projects, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The tool also involves visualization and interaction, which could potentially fall under human-computer interaction (cs.HC) and social and information networks (cs.SI). The tool could also involve aspects of information retrieval (cs.IR) in terms of searching for missing or unknown links between issues. Finally, the tool could potentially involve aspects of cybernetics (cs.CY) in terms of managing and controlling complex systems.
